headline: Why Palantir Stock Has Fallen 30% in a Month, and Why Continued Declines Are Inevitable
summary: Since closing at its all-time high share price of $124.62 on Feb. 18, Palantir (NASDAQ: PLTR) stock has headed almost straight back down.  Just four weeks ago, it seemed this company was every investor's favorite defense stock.  The Nasdaq Composite (NASDAQINDEX: ^IXIC) recently plunged 13.7% in about three weeks, and it's been a blow to investors in formerly red-hot tech stocks that have suddenly gone ice cold.

headline: Palantir Stock Has Fallen 30% From Its High. History Says This Will Happen Next.
summary: Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) shares advanced 340% in 2024 as the data analytics company reported strong financial results amid growing demand for its artificial intelligence (AI) platform.  History says Palantir still has a long way to fall.  Wall Street has been sounding the alarm on Palantir's valuation for months.
